ChatGPT said:
You're very close ğŸ‘ â€” now the DataContext is correct.

The current problem is this line:

ChangeText();
There is no method called ChangeText(), so the compiler will error.

âœ… Fix 1 â€” Just Increment the Variable
If your goal is to increase the number:

private void OnClick(object? sender, RoutedEventArgs e)
{
    Incrementation++;
}
âš ï¸ But Thereâ€™s One More Important Thing
Even though Incrementation increasesâ€¦

ğŸ‘‰ The UI will NOT update automatically.

Why?

Because the property does not notify the UI when it changes.

In Avalonia UI, bindings update only if the property raises change notifications.

âœ… Proper Working Version (With UI Updating)
Add INotifyPropertyChanged:

using Avalonia.Controls;
using Avalonia.Interactivity;
using System.ComponentModel;
using System.Runtime.CompilerServices;

namespace test1;

public partial class MainWindow : Window, INotifyPropertyChanged
{
    private int _incrementation = 0;

    public int Incrementation
    {
        get => _incrementation;
        set
        {
            _incrementation = value;
            OnPropertyChanged();
        }
    }

    public MainWindow()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        DataContext = this;
    }

    private void OnClick(object? sender, RoutedEventArgs e)
    {
        Incrementation++;
    }

    public event PropertyChangedEventHandler? PropertyChanged;

    private void OnPropertyChanged([CallerMemberName] string? name = null)
    {
        PropertyChanged?.Invoke(this, new PropertyChangedEventArgs(name));
    }
}
âœ… XAML Example
<StackPanel>
    <TextBlock Text="{Binding Incrementation}" FontSize="24"/>
    <Button Content="Increase" Click="OnClick"/>
</StackPanel>
Now when you click:

0 â†’ 1 â†’ 2 â†’ 3 â†’ ...
And the UI updates properly.

