ChatGPT said:
Ah â€” now I see exactly whatâ€™s happening ğŸ˜…

In Avalonia, Button hover styling is controlled by pseudo-classes like :pointerover and by the theme youâ€™re using (Fluent, Default, Simple).

If your Foreground is white and your Background is not set, the default hover style might make the Background white, which can â€œhideâ€ the button text â€” or if your button is small, it may even visually disappear.

âœ… Why This Happens
Avalonia buttons have a built-in hover effect in their theme.

If your Background or Foreground colors conflict with the theme, the text can blend into the hover background, giving the illusion the button disappears.

For example:

<Button Content="Click Me" Foreground="White"/>
With default theme, hovering may change the background to white, so white text disappears.

âœ… Fix 1 â€” Explicit Background
Set the buttonâ€™s Background explicitly:

<Button Content="Click Me"
        Foreground="White"
        Background="DarkBlue"
        FontSize="18"/>
Now on hover, the default theme will tint the background slightly, but the text stays visible.

âœ… Fix 2 â€” Define Hover Style Yourself
You can override hover behavior using Style and pseudo-class selector:

<Window.Styles>
    <Style Selector="Button:pointerover">
        <Setter Property="Background" Value="DarkGreen"/>
        <Setter Property="Foreground" Value="White"/>
    </Style>
</Window.Styles>
Now when you hover:

Background â†’ DarkGreen

Foreground â†’ White

No disappearing text.

âœ… Fix 3 â€” Use Resources for Themes
Define brushes in Window.Resources or App.axaml:

<SolidColorBrush x:Key="ButtonBackground" Color="DarkBlue"/>
<SolidColorBrush x:Key="ButtonForeground" Color="White"/>
<SolidColorBrush x:Key="ButtonHoverBackground" Color="DarkGreen"/>
Then style:

<Style Selector="Button">
    <Setter Property="Background" Value="{StaticResource ButtonBackground}"/>
    <Setter Property="Foreground" Value="{StaticResource ButtonForeground}"/>
</Style>

<Style Selector="Button:pointerover">
    <Setter Property="Background" Value="{StaticResource ButtonHoverBackground}"/>
</Style>
This is production-ready.

âš¡ TL;DR
Always set Foreground + Background explicitly if you override colors.

Avalonia hover can clash with default theme colors.

Use pseudo-class :pointerover to customize hover.

